h is a simple [TAP](https://testanything.org/) inspired macros collection

MACROs
-------
ok(expr, ...) 
Takes an expression if fails increase fail count and prints a not ok
if it passes prints ok and message if any

fails(...)
Fails directly and increase fail count and prints message. Good for 
pending implementations

pass(...)
Pass directly and prints any messages if any

diag(fmt, ...)
Helps to print diagnostics if you want any can be disaled by #define LOG 0

exit_status()
Exit with amount of fail tests it is good if you use a CI tool.

USAGE
--------
Add h.h to your source file and compile.
